title: MCU CosmicCast Episode 19: The James Gunn Saga Ends
body:
Welcome to the 19th episode of the MCU CosmicCast, the week that the long and winding James Gunn saga has finally come to close.

This week:

  • Chris Pratt says they want to move forward, while the James Gunn saga comes to a close and fans need to accept the final decision and not turn it into a “movement” that will get Marvel fandom mocked like another fandom recently did.
  • Antoine Fuquais meeting…

summary: Is Captain Marvel gonna go with the space alien origin? Because, if it does, I'm gonna be pretty ill about Tony trying to tell...
body: Is Captain Marvel gonna go with the space alien origin? Because, if it does, I’m gonna be pretty ill about Tony trying to tell people about another space attack and them pushing it to the side like it means nothing. I mean, I’m already mad about it because it’s not like aliens coming to fight on and/or against Earth is a new concept for anyone in the MCU, so, them not listening already doesn’t make any sense. But, if they go with that origin, I’m gonna be feeling some type of way and there’s gonna be words.

summary:
The Life of Captain Marvel #2 Publisher: Marvel Comics 

(W) Margaret Stohl (A) Carlos Pacheco, Marguerite Sauvage (CA) Julian...
caption:
The Life of Captain Marvel #2

Publisher: Marvel Comics
(W) Margaret Stohl (A) Carlos Pacheco, Marguerite Sauvage (CA) Julian Totino TedescoTHE DEFINITIVE ORIGIN OF CAPTAIN MARVEL!
For years, Carol Danvers has been at the front lines, protecting Earth and her fellow heroes from harm. Then one visit to her childhood home changed everything. Now her brother’s in a coma, and until he’s safe, Captain Marvel…is standing down. But while Carol may not be looking for danger, it’s looking for her. A weapon has been unleashed. And Carol’s sleepy coastal town is about to become the center of its world. Margaret Stohl and Carlos Pacheco tear apart Captain Marvel’s whole universe in part two of an origin-defining tale!

In Shops: Aug 22, 2018
